                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G Women’s Rights/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hull</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-22T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 22, 1933—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>114. Department’s 104, 10 p.m., December 19. For the information of the committee
                    on revision of nationality laws, please advise whether the Convention on
                    Nationality which you signed was the same as that given on page 50 (Topic 8) of
                    Document No. 4 for the use of the Delegates published by the Pan American Union.
                    If materially different, please telegraph full text.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
